    {

        "\n",
        "# Standardizing the feature set\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "algo_1 = LogisticRegression(random_state=42)\n",
        "algo_1.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Predictions and evaluation\n",
        "y_pred_algo_1 = algo_1.predict(X_test)\n",
        "accuracy_algo_1 = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_algo_1)\n",
        "conf_matrix_algo_1 = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_algo_1)\n",
        "kappa_algo_1 = cohen_kappa_score(y_test, y_pred_algo_1)\n",
        "rmse_algo_1 = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_algo_1))\n",
        "relative_absolute_error_algo_1 = np.sum(np.abs(y_test - y_pred_algo_1)) / np.sum(np.abs(y_test - y_test.mean()))\n",
        "root_relative_squared_error_algo_1 = np.sqrt(np.sum((y_test - y_pred_algo_1) ** 2) / np.sum((y_test - y_test.mean()) ** 2))\n",
        "total_instances = len(y_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "algo_1_results = {\n",
        "    \"Model\": \"Logistic Regression\",\n",
        "    \"Accuracy\": accuracy_algo_1,\n",
        "    \"Correctly Classified Instances\": np.sum(y_test == y_pred_algo_1),\n",
        "    \"Incorrectly Classified Instances\": np.sum(y_test != y_pred_algo_1),\n",
        "    \"Kappa Statistic\": kappa_algo_1,\n",
        "    \"Root Mean Squared Error\": rmse_algo_1,\n",
        "    \"Relative Absolute Error\": relative_absolute_error_algo_1,\n",
        "    \"Root Relative Squared Error\": root_relative_squared_error_algo_1,\n",
        "    \"Total Instances\": total_instances\n",
        "}\n",

        "algo_1_results"

        "# Compile results from all models\n",
        "results = [\n",
        "    algo_1_results, algo_2_results, algo_3_results, algo_4_results\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Displaying the comparison chart for all models' accuracy\n",
        "model = [result['Model'] for result in results]\n",
        "accuracy_score = [result['Accuracy'] for result in results]\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 5))\n",
        "bars = plt.barh(model, accuracy_score, color='skyblue')\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Accuracy\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Model Comparison by Accuracy\")\n",
        "plt.xlim(0, 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adding value labels\n",
        "for bar, accuracy in zip(bars, accuracy_score):\n",
        "    plt.text(accuracy / 2, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height() / 2, f\"{accuracy:.2f}\", ha='center', va='center', color='black')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.show()"
